author: ericf
msg: Check in preprocess() method whether element/attribute properties of
the bean-being-generated are Enum types.  If any of them are, add
them to a set. Then, during actual generation, check for an entry
in this set for any simpleValue types when emitting code that
would obtain a reference to an enum.  If one is found, generate
code that uses the public static forString(value) method on
the enum class rather than the protected constructor, which
is not for use outside of the enum's class hierarchy.
